                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4909.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-13T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In pursuance of Department’s September 12, 8 p.m., I called upon Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs this morning and made urgent representations relative to the
                    unfortunate results which might follow at Aguaprieta and Nogales, should firing
                    across the line not be prevented. He authorized me to telegraph the Department
                    that immediate and energetic steps will be taken to prevent any such occurrences
                    at either place. I left with him a clear memorandum on the subject and believe
                    that the matter will be diligently attended to.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
